# Project rules

1. We are targeting home assistant versions 2025.1 and above. 
2. We are using Peplink routers version 8.1.1 and above.
3. We are building a home assistant custom integration to talk to a Peplink router through it's local API. 
4. We will use documented and some undocumented APIs. 

# Coding standards

1. Adhere to home assistant development practices and guidelines.
2. Use type hints and mypy for type checking.
3. Use asyncio for async operations.
4. Use async/await for async functions.

# Structure

1. We will build a fully self-contained API client for the Peplink API. 
2. There will be a script called standalone_test.py that will use only this API client to fetch and print the WAN status.
3. The home assistant integration will use the same API client and populate the sensors we need.

# How I want to work 

1. Be surgical with changes. Avoid refactors unless specifically prompted.
2. Never prompt me to perform git/github actions.
3. Never prompt me to restart home assistant.

# The Peplink Local API

### Official API documentation

Documentation: https://download.peplink.com/resources/Peplink-Router-API-Documentation-for-Firmware-8.1.1.pdf

#### APIs used by this integration

##### Reading device information
- /api/status.client -- Get client information for device_tracker

Example response: 
```json
{
  "list": [
    {
      "ip": "192.168.211.2",
      "connectionType": "ethernet",
      "lease": {
        "expiresIn": 53128,
        "type": "dhcp"
      },
      "name": "UDM Pro WAN1",
      "mac": "78:45:58:86:BA:6D",
      "active": true,
      "vlanId": 100
    },
    {
      "ip": "192.168.212.2",
      "connectionType": "ethernet",
      "lease": {
        "expiresIn": 53228,
        "type": "dhcp"
      },
      "name": "UDM Pro WAN2",
      "mac": "78:45:58:86:BA:6C",
      "active": true,
      "vlanId": 110
    }
  ],
  "client": [
    {
      "ip": "192.168.211.2",
      "connectionType": "ethernet",
      "lease": {
        "expiresIn": 53128,
        "type": "dhcp"
      },
      "name": "UDM Pro WAN1",
      "mac": "78:45:58:86:BA:6D",
      "active": true,
      "vlanId": 100
    },
    {
      "ip": "192.168.212.2",
      "connectionType": "ethernet",
      "lease": {
        "expiresIn": 53228,
        "type": "dhcp"
      },
      "name": "UDM Pro WAN2",
      "mac": "78:45:58:86:BA:6C",
      "active": true,
      "vlanId": 110
    }
  ]
}
```

